*Galax aphylla* L. (Handwritten: Diapensiaceae)
"Galax"

Salt Pond Mountain, War Spur Trail, off
West Virginia road near Mt. Lake Biological
Station, elevation 3750 feet.

Herbaceous: White flowers on spike-like
clusters, 3-4 mm broad; heart-shaped
leaves. Grows in dry woods.
